<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 07 at 3:19AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONCERNS THIS AFTERNOON...
An anomalously dry airmass for early April will settle over the
region today. As temperatures rise into the mid to upper 50s this
afternoon, minimum relative humidities will drop to 20 to 30
percent. This combined with northwest winds gusts from 25 to 30
mph will result in elevated fire weather concerns this afternoon.
While conditions will support elevated fire weather potential
today, conditions have not been deemed critical enough to warrant
a red flag warning thanks to recent substantial rainfall over
these aras.</description>
